  "schema_version": 1.4,
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Cyclops Seeker",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Cyclopean Researchers",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 82",
                "aonid": 274,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 82",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane",
              "page": 82,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "It's not often a cyclops makes their way into Avistan, but those interested in learning for its own sake might seek out places of higher education to conduct obscure avenues of research for their own edification. The presence of an enormous, one-eyed giant can be quite alarming, and others' panic is not conducive toward quiet study or long-term research. Accordingly, these cyclops seekers often develop methods of changing their shape to fit in more easily among the societies they wish to learn from.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 82",
            "aonid": 274,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane pg. 82",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Pathfinder #218: Titanbane",
          "page": 82,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Some cyclopes pursue knowledge, power, and artifacts from a bygone era\u2014particularly those recovered from regions where ancient cyclops nations once stood. These cyclops seekers hone their brief insights into epiphanic bursts of inspiration to better uncover forgotten truths. A rare few become philosophers and sages, whether as secluded hermits or as gregarious guides eager to share the wonders they've discovered. These talents are more common among the introspective cyclopes of Iblydos.   \n  \nCyclops seekers are particularly fond of collecting scrolls, grimoires, and other objects of magical lore\u2014even accidentally foregoing rest and meals when devouring esoteric textbooks, historical documents, and fiction. Those with a good sense of humor realize the irony of trading their physical hunger for their eternal thirst for knowledge, though failure to achieve a breakthrough can lead a cyclops to ruminate, becoming sullen and withdrawn. When they're too large to safely study an interesting set of more compact ruins, a cyclops seeker might hire on smaller adventurers as reconnaissance teams or research assistants, but woe to those who doublecross their scholarly employers, for while the cyclops seeker is a studious creature, they're also deadly in battle.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
